The notifications in Confluence includes Watches, Favourites and Daily Report. By right, users without email address should not be able to subscribe to any form of notifications. Currently, there is no validations for this taking place in Confluence. As a result, users without emails are not notified and the logs indicates this WARN-ing:

{noformat}
2009-06-22 10:48:18,892 WARN [DefaultQuartzScheduler_Worker-8] [confluence.mail.jobs.DailyReportJob] doExecute Not sending notification email [ Confluence Changes in the last 24 hours+ ] to [ ghost ]:  No email set
{noformat}

It would be great if Confluence at least informs the users that they did not specify their email address rather than leaving a warning in the logs every time the notifications being sent out. Perhaps, this can be done by validating the email field before allowing the user to subscribe in Confluence.

