In my admin area the following warning is displayed

 Base URL either contains an IP address or is set to 'localhost': http://wiki.kwb.localhost:8081. The server may not accessible from the network. Configure Base URL. (Do not remind me again)

I understand the idea of this message. However, it is only justified if the URL servername is just localhost. We use "localhost" as a pseudo TLD, as in wiki.xyz.localhost. Using "localhost" as a pseudo TLD in Intranets (Microsoft focused companies usually use .local) is common, so the message is not justified and should not display. IMHO it should only display if localhost is the servername.

