The macro browser provides an i18n key to specify the description for a macro
{code}
{pluginKey}.{macroName}.desc 
{code}

But this value get overriden by the value provided in the <description> attribute of the macro.  You can put an i18n key into this description element which gets converted correctly within the macro browser, but doesn't get converted in the plugin administration section or the plugin repository.

